## What was implemented\
\
### Docs (`docs-ecosystem`)\
- `docs/DEPLOYMENT-ECOSYSTEM.md` \'97 single buyer-facing map of all deployment levels (local dev, self-hosted, vendor-hosted, end client, source license), platform roles and costs, environment variable reference\
- `docs/DISTRIBUTION-REPOS.md` \'97 dev vs release repo split, what goes where, release workflow, buyer access model, CHANGELOG format\
- `docs/DEMO-INSTANCE.md` \'97 full Railway provisioning checklist, nightly reset options (Railway cron, GitHub Action, HTTP trigger), Early Access lead export, rate limiting policy\
- `EULA.md` \'97 proprietary license draft (marked for attorney review before first sale)\
- `CHANGELOG.md` \'97 buyer-facing changelog starting at v0.10.0\
\
### Seed data (`seed-package`)\
- `scripts/seed-demo.ts` \'97 idempotent script that populates: workspace, demo admin user, "Acme Plumbing & HVAC" site, a published blog post, a social batch with 3 pending variants (LinkedIn, X, Facebook), one promoted LinkedIn draft. Supports `--reset` (wipe + re-seed, MongoDB only) and `--buyer` (buyer onboarding variant with random temp password and onboarding checklist).\
\
### Backend demo mode (`demo-mode-backend`)\
- `src/demo/middleware.ts` \'97 `demoGuard` middleware blocks bootstrap, integrations write, real publish, site delete, and WordPress import when `DEMO_MODE=1`. Also exports `demoAiLimiter` (20 req/IP/hour for AI routes in demo mode).\
- `src/api/early-access.ts` \'97 `POST /api/early-access` with `express-rate-limit` (5/hour in demo mode). Upserts leads to `early_access_leads` Mongo collection. Optional Resend notify via `RESEND_EARLY_ACCESS_NOTIFY`.\
- `src/api/auth.ts` \'97 Added `GET /api/demo/session` (rate-limited, only active when `DEMO_MODE=1`). Issues a real session token for `demo@freshpress.com` without requiring credentials.\
- `src/auth/types.ts` \'97 Added `isDemo?: boolean` to `AuthContext` and `AuthMeResponse`.\
- `src/hosted/validate.ts` \'97 Demo mode skips `MASTER_KEY` requirement at boot.\
- `src/server.ts` \'97 Mounts `demoGuard`, `demoAiLimiter`, and `earlyAccessRouter`.\
\
### Frontend demo mode (`demo-mode-frontend`)\
- `editor/src/components/DemoBanner.tsx` \'97 sticky banner with "Demo" badge, "changes reset nightly" message, and "Get Early Access" button. Clicking opens an email capture modal that POSTs to `/api/early-access`.\
- `editor/src/context/AuthContext.tsx` \'97 Added `isDemo?: boolean` to `AuthState`.\
- `editor/src/App.tsx` \'97 `isDemoHost()` detection (checks hostname or `?demo=1`). On demo hosts, calls `GET /api/demo/session` before showing anything, auto-logs in, and renders the dashboard directly. `DemoBanner` renders when `auth.isDemo` is true.\
- `editor/src/index.css` \'97 Styles for `.demo-banner`, `.demo-modal-overlay`, `.demo-modal`, and shared `.btn` modifiers.\
\
### Buyer onboarding (`buyer-onboarding-seed`)\
- `scripts/provision-buyer.ts` \'97 Handoff template now includes the `seed-demo.ts --buyer` command for post-provision seeding.\
- `docs/BUYER-SETUP.md` \'97 Updated to describe the sample site, AI provider setup, and link to ecosystem docs.\
\
### Release workflow (`release-repo`)\
- `scripts/promote-release.sh` \'97 Runnable shell script: validates clean `main`, runs `npm test && npm run build`, creates a git tag, pushes it to `freshpress-release` remote, creates a GitHub Release if `gh` CLI is available and a `CHANGELOG.md` entry exists. Supports `--init` for first-time force-push.\
- `.gitattributes` \'97 Marks `data/vendor/`, `ref/prompts/`, `scripts/promote-release.sh`, and `.env*` as `export-ignore` so they're stripped from GitHub archive/zip downloads.\
\
### Railway provisioning (`demo-railway`)\
The code is complete and ready. The actual Railway service creation for `demo.freshpress.com` is a one-time ops task \'97 the full checklist is in `docs/DEMO-INSTANCE.md`.\
